Everyone should check this place out at least once to see if it's their jam, especially if you love Rum, but otherwise not a great place to go I guess unless you're such a favored usual that the bartenders will prioritize you over the dozens of people getting tall flaming long island ice teas in tiki mugs with life sized umbrellas and a flamingo - which I want to stress are great, but not when you're waiting for one to finish when it isn't yours.

Cute space, well themed, well-decóred - overall good vibes. Was there for an "I Heart Burlesque" show - featuring a variety of burlesque artists and the event was sponsored by some rum company.  My party and I arrived about 15 minutes before the show was scheduled and the space was pretty full. The food looked and smelled delicious, and judging by some of the other reviews, it probably tastes good too.  That said, this place DEFINITELY has a management/service issue. I was originally going to write-off last night's experience as just a "bad night" but after reading MANY others' review, there seems to be a pattern. There were 3-4 people behind the bar at any given time, however, only 2 were actively making drinks and they were not particularly responsive and worked really slowly. I mean, I get you have some complicated drinks on the menu, and that's fine, but at least acknowledge everyone else who's standing around waiting to make eye contact (also, if you're gonna have a major event with an influx of patrons, perhaps make a toned-down menu with easier cocktails? Just a management suggestion).  The 2 other folks who were behind the bar were just there collecting and cleaning glasses - in fact one of them had to insist that they were "only a bar-back" and couldn't help with taking an order, or even splitting a $5 to make change. Like, you're (the venue) hosting an event - with the plan to make money and increase revenue - and then severely under-staff the bar, and have insufficient amount of bills in the register so that people could leave tips to their servers and the burlesque artists - that's just REALLY REALLY POOR PLANNING (and frankly undermines the point of having a SPONSORED event, and frankly suggests a deep lack of respect for your patrons).  Then, to add insult to injury, it took 20 minutes (I wish I was exaggerating, but I timed it) for us to get acknowledged and have 3 drinks served. One of them was a Sazerac (the other two were simple, a vodka soda and scotch on the rocks) - the minute the bartender asked if I wanted it on the rocks or straight up, I should have just changed my order.  If you don't know that a Sazerac is SUPPOSED to be served SUPER CHILLED and STRAIGHT, then you have NO BUSINESS MAKING THE DRINK. After I had clarified that I'd like it super cold and straight, I received a *clear* drink, lukewarm, with a lemon twist (I'll take responsibility for this one - that's on me, I should have known better).  It did NOT taste like a Sazerac. It wasn't a Sazerac. I drank it in silence, because I didn't want to deal with having this corrected and having to deal with the bartender's attitude when I eventually would get their attention again.  Of course, the standoffish attitudes coming off the 2 bartenders who were actively making drinks didn't help (as if they were doing ME a favor for being there and I was annoying them with my drink order), but I'm just chalking that up to being understaffed and overworked for the evening - but this does seem to be a pattern at this place.  Overall, I like the space, but the service really puts a major ding on the experience. Unless this improves significantly, I don't really see myself coming back here.

Normally I love this restaurant, they have great food and the customer service is usually great, usually being the operative word. On July 6, 2018 I placed an order via Grubhub. I was informed my order would be delivered in about 1 hr, which is typical and I would never complain about that. I waited and waited and after an hour and a half passed I have them the benefit of the doubt and figured it’s friday night, must be busy. Once it approached 2 hours with no contact however, I called the restaurant directly to track the order progress. At which time I was told by whomever answered the phone that they had attempted to deliver the order and made two attempts to call and contact as well as informing Grubhub who also apparently tried to contact and got no response. At that point I informed the gentleman that I had not received any missed calls or texts about my order. I asked the man to repeat the number they had on file for my account and sure enough it was correct so I’m not sure why I had no missed calls registered. I chose to contact Grubhub directly. Immediately after hanging up I placed a call to Grubhub and informed them of the situation. I was told by the representative that it stated that delivery had been attempted but that NO communication had been on the restaurant side or by Grubhub. After I concluded my first call with Grubhub, luck would have it that their customer service line called to let me know that the restaurant had tried to deliver but was unsuccessful. I asked the young lady if they had just received a call from the restaurant and she confirmed which would suggest that the man was dishonest about previously contacting Grubhub. This more than anything was what upset me and despite the great food, I WILL NOT order from this restaurant again. I am very disappointed with the customer service and hopefully the restaurant management can address issues like this so they don’t occur in the future.

place is all sorts of awesome. 90's hip hop blasting, French bartenders, cricket bitters in tiki cocktails, and random flicks projected on the wall. kudos to being as weird as Brooklyn is.
